Indentation is off:
```suggestion
  apply Polynomial.splits_of_comp (algebraMap F (algebraicClosure F E))
    (algebraMap (algebraicClosure F E) E) g
  simp only [mem_roots']
  intro r âŸ¨_, hrmâŸ©
  simp only [IsRoot.def, Polynomial.eval_map] at hrm
  simp only [RingHom.mem_range, IntermediateField.algebraMap_apply, Subtype.exists, exists_prop',
    nonempty_prop, exists_eq_right]
  exact âŸ¨minpoly F x, âŸ¨minpoly.monic h, hrmâŸ©âŸ©
```
and this main result holds for any polynomial, not just `minpoly` and can be [proven very easily](https://live.lean-lang.org/#).
Thank you very much! I'll generalize it at once.
